		"description": "<p>When you cast this spell, you utter a command word and transform one non-magical weapon into a mundane object of roughly equivalent size. For example you might change a dagger into a book or a sword into a broom. As a bonus action, a creature can grasp the item and utter the command word again to end the spell early, transforming the object back into its original weapon form.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Cast At Higher Levels. </strong>By using a 3rd-level spell slot, you can transform a common, uncommon, or rare magical weapon this way (though the object it becomes is still non-magical). A 4th level spell slot can transform a very rare weapon, and a 5th-level can transform a legendary weapon.</p>",
